## Web Research Complete

**Queries**: 4 searches executed  
**Sources**: 7 relevant sources found  
**Artifact**: `/home/asiri/.archon/workspaces/alexsiri7/reli/artifacts/runs/2671bff16b99afd42ffc8dcfacb3593f/web-research.md`

### Key Findings

- **Root cause confirmed**: `RAILWAY_TOKEN` in GitHub Actions secret has expired/become invalid — Railway API returns `Not Authorized`. This is the 4th recurrence (#733, #739, #742, #751).
- **No automatic rotation exists**: GitHub secrets don't auto-rotate. Railway token rotation requires a human with railway.com dashboard access. Agents cannot perform this step.
- **Critical fix detail**: The token must be created with **"No expiration"** explicitly selected — Railway's dashboard default TTL is short, which is why tokens keep expiring after each rotation.
- **Weekly health check already in place** (`railway-token-health.yml` from #753) but its Monday-only cadence doesn't prevent mid-week outages.
- **Existing runbook** at `docs/RAILWAY_TOKEN_ROTATION_742.md` covers the exact steps: create token → `gh secret set RAILWAY_TOKEN` → rerun CI run `25019840901`.

### Gaps

- Railway doesn't document exact account token TTL — only community reports confirm they expire
- The token type conflict (account vs project token) is unresolved in Railway docs; current workflow needs an account token

Sources:
- [Railway Public API Docs](https://docs.railway.com/integrations/api)
- [Railway Login & Tokens](https://docs.railway.com/integrations/oauth/login-and-tokens)
- [RAILWAY_TOKEN invalid or expired — Railway Help Station](https://station.railway.com/questions/railway-token-invalid-or-expired-59011e20)
- [Using Github Actions with Railway](https://blog.railway.com/p/github-actions)
- [Best Practices for Managing Secrets in GitHub Repositories](https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/168661)
- [API Token "Not Authorized" Error — Railway Help Station](https://station.railway.com/questions/api-token-not-authorized-error-for-pub-82b4ccf1)
